defaultProtecting children in onlinedefault and mobiledefault environmentsdefaultPEGI has been recognised by the UK government as a leading example of an industry taking a responsible approach 
defaultin
default keeping children away from unsuitable content, and 
defaultalso 
defaulthas 
defaultstrong recognition amongst UK parents.
default It 
defaulthas 
defaultnow 
defaultexpanded into the online games market through PEGI Online. As part of the rating process online game providers must indicate if their gaming environments fulfil rigorous PEGI Online requirements which are s
defaultet out in 
defaultarticle 9 of 
defaultthe PEGI Code of Conduct. These are:
default9.1 
defaultRated Content
default:
default Products offering Online Ga
defaultmeplay Environments operated by 
defaultSignatories will, where practicable, be appropriately rated under the PEGI System. This provision will not apply to ga
defaultme content which is posted on the Online Gameplay Environment operated by the User but which is not under the User’s control, such as user-generated content. 
default9.2 Removal of Undesirable Content
default:
default Signatories shall use their best endeavours to ensure that On
defaultline Gameplay Environments are kept free of content which is illegal, offensive, racist, degrading, corrupting, threatening, obscene or might permanently impair the development of minors.  When Online Gameplay Environments also contain 
defaultuser generated conte
defaultnt, Signatories shall use their best endeavours to immediately take down any such content which is illegal, offensive, racist, degrading, corrupting, threatening, obscene or might permanently impair the development of minors. Observance of all the foregoin
defaultg should, where possible, also include removal of undesirable links or ‘hyperlinks.’ 
default9.3 Appropriate Reporting Mechanisms
default:
default Consistent with the foregoing paragraph, Signatories will ensure that appropriate reporting mechanisms are in place to allow players
default to notify Signatories of the existence of content such as described in the previous sub-section within any Online Gameplay Environment.
default9.4 Chatrooms:
default Signatories should take reasonable precautions to ensure that Online Gameplay Environments which allow v
defaultoice or video chat, protect children from access to age-inappropriate content introduced by other users.
default9.5 Other Operators:
default Signatories shall use their best endeavours to ensure that operators of Online Gameplay Environments offered by Products published
default by the User and which are authorised by, but not under the control of, the User, abide by these rules and/or subsequently become Signatories themselves.
default9.6 Safety Warnings
default:
default Signatories shall advise users of Online Gameplay Environments under their contro
defaultl of the desirability of taking occasional breaks from Online Gameplay.  
default9.7 Community Standards:
default Signatories shall ensure the incorporation in their terms of business with users of Online Gameplay Environments of certain provisions usually included under the heading of so called ‘community standards’. These provisions will contain prohibitions agains
defaultt those users introducing content or indulging in online behaviour which is illegal, offensive, racist, degrading, corrupting, threatening, obscene or might permanently impair the development of minors.
default9.8 P
defaultrivacy:
default Any User engaging in the online collecti
defaulton of personal information from subscribers will maintain an effective and coherent Privacy Policy fully in accordance
defaultUkie work closely with PEGI to ensure that this system works for games companies, and to continue strengthening and improving it
default.
